lacking the intron and the reporter gene. The yeast transformants obtained 
through introductions of these plasmids showed beta-galactosidase activity and 
the activity conferred by YEp3'NCR-lacZ was about 50% of that conferred by 
YEp3'UTR-lacZ. The primer extension analysis showed that transcription of the 
reporter gene on both plasmids starts at three alternative sites all of which 
are located within the downstream CT-motif, suggesting a role for the unusual 
structure of the CT/AG-biased sequence in the initiation of transcription.

